Torsten provides four storage profiles sized to maximize available system memory: # Select a profile via CLI
./torsten-node run --storage-profile high-memory ... # Override individual parameters
./torsten-node run --storage-profile low-memory --utxo-block-cache-size-mb 4096 ... Profiles can also be set in the node configuration file: { "storage": { "profile": "high-memory", "utxoBlockCacheSizeMb": 8192 }
} Resolution order: profile defaults < config file overrides < CLI overrides.

